","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to slaughter","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَمَآ أَكَلَ ٱلسَّبُعُ إِلَّا مَا ذَكَّيْتُمْ وَمَا ذُبِحَ عَلَى ٱلنُّصُبِ","english":"You shall not eat that from which a wild animal has eaten, except what you [are able to] ritually slaughter [before its death] and what is slit up on the altars."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set fire on","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"In the sense of setting fire causative to ذَكَا (ḏakā, “to flare up”), in the sense of slaughtering probably a loan from Jewish Aramaic, the geminate verb דַּכֵּי (dakkē) usually meaning to “to purify ritually, to clean by separation”, see as well the semantic history of زَكَاة (zakāh)."},"ipa":["/ðak.kaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13959","headword_ar":"ذَكِىٌّ","root":"*kw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to musk, and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiy~apN","text_ar":"ذَكِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misokN","text_ar":"مِسْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is said by IAmb, is both masc. and fem., and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanobarN","text_ar":"عَنْبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAkK","text_ar":"ذَاكٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diffusing odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a strong"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pungent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See 1, second sentence.]) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iHapN *akiy~apN","text_ar":"رَايِحَةٌ ذَكِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pungent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odour"},{"kind":"text","text":"[whether sweet or fetid]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAd~apN","text_ar":"حَادَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hd","text_ar":"حد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the attribute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akaA='","text_ar":"ذَكَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acuteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of intel-ligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (K, TA, &c.:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*okiyaA='u","text_ar":"اَذْكِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) It is also, sometimes, applied to a camel [or the like, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp in spirit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^aAdN","text_ar":"فُوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slaughtered in the manner prescribed by the law, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aboHN","text_ar":"ذَبْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akaApN","text_ar":"ذَكَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and [therefore] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN *akiY~N","text_ar":"شَاةٌ ذَكِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, slaughtered in the manner above mentioned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akaAp","text_ar":"ذَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter in that manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one has attained"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while life yet remained therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 2]: (Mgh, Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiy~apN","text_ar":"ذَكِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as its fem.] is extr. [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHapN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilodN *akiY~N","text_ar":"جِلْدٌ ذَكِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A skin stripped from an animal that has been slaughtered in the manner mentioned above."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n13964","headword_ar":"ذَكِىٌّ","root":"Quasi *kY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*kw","text_ar":"ذكو"},{"kind":"text","text":","}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}